Electron-Beam Lithography Tool

Overview Our electron-beam lithography tool enables the precise fabrication of nanoscale patterns on silicon wafers. It involves shooting electrons through carbon nanotubes, focusing the beam, and exposing a silicon wafer covered with a photoresist chemical. Subsequent development dissolves the exposed parts, allowing the creation of customizable patterns and electrical circuits on a nanoscale. Current Tasks
Electronics

We are currently testing and developing the current sensing system to track the electron flow...

Software (Back End)

Development of software that translates nanoscale patterns into a sequence of silicon wafer and electron-beam actuations. Connection with the picomotor for wafer movement is underway.

Software (Front End)

Creation of a user-friendly GUI to draw the desired patterns, connected to the back-end system...

Theoretical Simulation (COMSOL + Theory)

Simulation of electron beam flow in COMSOL to predict focal length and spot size. Comparison with a theoretical simulator for validation.

Theoretical Simulation (Custom Software)

Development of custom software to simulate the end-to-end behavior of the entire system.
